Black Bean Soup

Ingredients
1/2 table spoon (or less) neutral oil
2 large or 3 medium cloves of garlic diced
1 large onion diced

3 tablespoons chile powder
1 tablespoon cumin

Two cans black beans (plain)
32 oz. Chicken broth/stock

pinch of salt as needed
1/4 milk or cream

Instructions
1. Place medium size pot on medium heat (5) , add oil, garlic, after a minute
    add onion. Saute onion until transparent.
2. Add chile powder and cumin, mix throughly for 1 minute.
3. Add black beans.
4. Add chicken broth.
5. Bring pot to a boil, reduce heat (4), cover, and continue to cook with a
    hard-simmer for 60 minutes. Add additional water if need to keep beans
    covered.
6. Purree soup unitl smooth, adjust salt if needed.
7. Add milk or cream and puree until incorprated.
